org.matsim.contrib.common.stats

Class StatsWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.contrib.common.stats.StatsWriter

  • public class StatsWriter
extends Object
    Utility functions for writing distributions and histograms to plain text files (for further plotting or processing in statistics software).

    illenberger

        Writes a plain text file with two columns where the first column contains the map keys and second the map values. Rows are sorted according to the natural order of the map keys.
        Parameters:
        map - a map (histogram)
        keyCol - the header for the first column
        valCol - the header for the second column
        file - a filename

      • writeLabeledHistogram

        public static void writeLabeledHistogram(gnu.trove.map.hash.TObjectDoubleHashMap<String> map,
                                         String keyCol,
                                         String valCol,
                                         String file,
                                         boolean sortByValues)
                                  throws IOException
        Writes a plain text file with two columns where the first column contains the map keys and second the map values. If sortByValues is true, row are sorted according to the natural order of the map values, otherwise rows are sorted by the natural order of the map keys.
        Parameters:
        map - a map (labeled histogram)
        keyCol - the header for the first column
        valCol - the header for the second column
        file - a filename
        sortByValues - if true the rows are sorted by map values, otherwise by key values
        Throws:
        IOException

      • writeBoxplot

        public static void writeBoxplot(gnu.trove.map.hash.TDoubleObjectHashMap<double[]> table,
                                String file)
                         throws IOException
        Writes a table with one column for each map entry. Columns are filled with the list of values in each map entry. Column headers are the map keys. For instance, use this function to create boxplots.
        Parameters:
        table - a map with a list of samples as value
        file - the filename
        Throws:
        IOException

      • writeScatterPlot

        public static void writeScatterPlot(gnu.trove.map.hash.TDoubleObjectHashMap<org.apache.commons.math.stat.descriptive.DescriptiveStatistics> table,
                                    String file)
                             throws IOException
        Writes a plain text file with two columns. The first columns contains the map keys, the second the values in the DescriptiveStatistics object value. For each key, rows are repeated for all values in the DescriptiveStatistics object.
        Parameters:
        table - a map with samples stored in a DescriptiveStatistics object
        file - the filename
        Throws:
        IOException

      • writeStatistics

                                   String keyLabel,
                                   String file)
                            throws IOException
        Writes a table with columns map-key and statistical indicators mean, median, min, max and number of samples. Rows are sorted according to the natural order of the map keys.

        file - the filename
        Throws:
        IOException
